  <p><strong>How we evaluate:</strong> We score each grinder on <strong>brew quality</strong>, <strong>grinder consistency</strong>, <strong>usability</strong>, <strong>cleaning burden</strong>, and <strong>value for money</strong>. For this SERP, we also weight grind speed and realistic espresso fit under $100.</p>

  <section>
    <h2 id="product-picks">Product picks by budget tier</h2>

    <h3>$0-$50 tier winner: Timemore Chestnut C2</h3>
    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Best for beginners who want cleaner filter cups without overthinking adjustment settings.</p>
    <p><strong>Buy this if...</strong> you mostly brew pour over, AeroPress, or French press and want the easiest under-$50 recommendation.</p>
    <p><strong>Skip this if...</strong> you need repeatable non-pressurized espresso dialing.</p>
    <ProsCons
      pros={["Strong grind consistency for the entry tier.", "Low effort and predictable daily workflow.", "Easy to clean with minimal tools."]}
      cons={["Internal adjustment is slower to change between brew styles.", "Espresso range is too coarse for demanding setups."]}
